

@i{History}: Was introduced in version 3.2, Nova 2.1 (2011)

Generalizations are ways of thinking about topics in more general terms. They are somewhat like
container `types' or `classes' in hierarchical modelling, but they need not be mutually
exclusive categories.

Generalizations may be used in topic-lifting, a kind of brain-storming
about issues, when searching for diagnostic explanations.
